// Template for Config.xcconfig (the real file is gitignored).
//
// Fresh-clone setup:
//   cp Config.xcconfig.example Config.xcconfig
//   # then paste your real keys into Config.xcconfig
//
// `REVENUECAT_API_KEY` is a plain build setting. Info.plist references it as
// `$(REVENUECAT_API_KEY)` and Xcode expands it at build time
// (INFOPLIST_EXPAND_BUILD_SETTINGS, on by default). NOTE: the `INFOPLIST_KEY_*`
// auto-merge does NOT work for custom keys — it only covers Apple-defined keys
// like NSPhotoLibraryUsageDescription — so the key must live in the physical
// Info.plist as a $() reference, not as `INFOPLIST_KEY_RevenueCatAPIKey`.
// The Swift side reads "RevenueCatAPIKey" from `Bundle.main` at launch
// (see `ImageCleanerApp.revenueCatAPIKey()`).
//
// Debug key talks to RevenueCat's Test Store (synthetic products, no money).
// Release key talks to real App Store (Sandbox under TestFlight, real
// billing in production). Both come from RevenueCat → Project Settings → API Keys.

REVENUECAT_API_KEY_DEBUG   = test_REPLACE_WITH_TEST_STORE_KEY
REVENUECAT_API_KEY_RELEASE = appl_REPLACE_WITH_PRODUCTION_KEY

// Per-configuration selection. `$(CONFIGURATION)` is Debug/Release at build
// time, so the `_$(CONFIGURATION)` suffix picks the right key.
REVENUECAT_API_KEY = $(REVENUECAT_API_KEY_$(CONFIGURATION:upper))
